  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Justification for the purpose and conditions of the intended stay?",
  "response": "Justification for the purpose and conditions of the intended stay typically refers to the explanation provided to immigration authorities or other relevant bodies to clarify the reasons for visiting a country and the circumstances surrounding the stay. This is often required for visa applications, residency permits, or entry clearances. Below are key points that could form part of this justification:\n\n### 1. **Purpose of Stay**\n   - **Tourism:** If the visit is for leisure, mention specific attractions, events, or activities you plan to engage in.\n   - **Business:** State the nature of the business activities (e.g., meetings, conferences, training) and provide details of the organizations involved.\n   - **Study:** Include acceptance letters from educational institutions, details of the course, and its duration.\n   - **Family Visit:** Explain your relationship with the host, the purpose of the visit (e.g., family reunion, special event), and the length of stay.\n   - **Medical Treatment:** Provide medical documentation, treatment plans, and details of the healthcare facility.\n\n### 2. **Conditions of Stay**\n   - **Duration:** Specify the exact dates of entry and departure, ensuring they align with the visa or permit requirements.\n   - **Accommodation:** Provide details of where you will stay (e.g., hotel booking confirmation, invitation letter from a host).\n   - **Financial Support:** Demonstrate that you have sufficient funds to cover expenses during your stay (e.g., bank statements, sponsorship letters).\n   - **Return Plans:** Provide evidence of ties to your home country (e.g., employment, family, property) to assure authorities that you intend to return.\n\n### 3. **Compliance with Regulations**\n   - **Legal Requirements:** Confirm that your stay will comply with the host country\u2019s laws and visa conditions (e.g., no unauthorized work).\n   - **Health and Safety:** If applicable, provide proof of health insurance or vaccinations required by the destination country.\n\n### 4. **Supporting Documents**\n   - Include all relevant documents such as passport, visa application form, invitation letters, travel itinerary, and proof of financial means.\n\n### Example Justification:\n\"I am applying for a Schengen visa to visit France for tourism purposes from [start date] to [end date]. During my stay, I plan to visit popular landmarks such as the Eiffel Tower and the Louvre Museum. I have booked accommodation at [hotel name] and will be funded by my personal savings, as evidenced by the attached bank statements. I have a stable job as a [job title] at [company name] and will return to my home country on [return date] to resume my responsibilities. I have no intention of overstaying my visa and will comply with all immigration regulations.\"\n\nThis justification should be tailored to your specific circumstances and supported by appropriate documentation to strengthen your application.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
